  "chapter": {
    "number": 9,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Paul’s Concern for the Jews"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "I speak the truth in Christ; I am not lying, as confirmed by my conscience in the Holy Spirit."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "I have deep sorrow and unceasing anguish in my heart."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "For I could wish that I myself were cursed and cut off from Christ for the sake of my brothers, my own flesh and blood,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "the people of Israel. Theirs is the adoption as sons; theirs the divine glory and the covenants; theirs the giving of the law, the temple worship, and the promises."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "Theirs are the patriarchs, and from them proceeds the human descent of Christ, who is God over all, forever worthy of praise!",
          {
            "noteId": 4672
          },
          "Amen."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Sovereign Choice"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "It is not as though God’s word has failed. For not all who are descended from Israel are Israel."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "Nor because they are Abraham’s descendants are they all his children. On the contrary, “Through Isaac your offspring will be reckoned.”",
          {
            "noteId": 4673
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "So it is not the children of the flesh who are God’s children, but it is the children of the promise who are regarded as offspring."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "For this is what the promise stated: “At the appointed time I will return, and Sarah will have a son.”",
          {
            "noteId": 4674
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "Not only that, but Rebecca’s children were conceived by one man, our father Isaac."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "Yet before the twins were born or had done anything good or bad, in order that God’s plan of election might stand,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "not by works but by Him who calls, she was told, “The older will serve the younger.”",
          {
            "noteId": 4675
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "So it is written: “Jacob I loved, but Esau I hated.”",
          {
            "noteId": 4676
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "What then shall we say? Is God unjust? Certainly not!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "For He says to Moses:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I will have mercy on whom I have mercy,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will have compassion on whom I have compassion.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4677
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "So then, it does not depend on man’s desire or effort, but on God’s mercy."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "For the Scripture says to Pharaoh: “I raised you up for this very purpose, that I might display My power in you, and that My name might be proclaimed in all the earth.”",
          {
            "noteId": 4678
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "Therefore God has mercy on whom He wants to have mercy, and He hardens whom He wants to harden."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "One of you will say to me, “Then why does God still find fault? For who can resist His will?”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          "But who are you, O man, to talk back to God? Shall what is formed say to Him who formed it, “Why did You make me like this?”",
          {
            "noteId": 4679
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "Does not the potter have the right to make from the same lump of clay one vessel for special occasions and another for common use?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "What if God, intending to show His wrath and make His power known, bore with great patience the vessels of His wrath, prepared for destruction?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          "What if He did this to make the riches of His glory known to the vessels of His mercy, whom He prepared in advance for glory—"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          "including us, whom He has called not only from the Jews, but also from the Gentiles?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          "As He says in Hosea:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I will call them ‘My People’ who are not My people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will call her ‘My Beloved’ who is not My beloved,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4680
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          "and,",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“It will happen that in the very place where it was said to them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘You are not My people,’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will be called",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘sons of the living God.’”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4681
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          "Isaiah cries out concerning Israel:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Though the number of the Israelites is like the sand of the sea,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "only the remnant will be saved.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the Lord will carry out His sentence on the earth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "thoroughly and decisively.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4682
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          "It is just as Isaiah foretold:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Unless the Lord of Hosts had left us descendants,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we would have become like Sodom,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "we would have resembled Gomorrah.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4683
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel’s Unbelief"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          "What then will we say? That the Gentiles, who did not pursue righteousness, have obtained it, a righteousness that is by faith;"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          "but Israel, who pursued a law of righteousness, has not attained it."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          "Why not? Because their pursuit was not by faith, but as if it were by works. They stumbled over the stumbling stone,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          "as it is written:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“See, I lay in Zion a stone of stumbling",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a rock of offense;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4684
          },
          {
            "text": "and the one who believes in Him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will never be put to shame.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4685
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
